# 🔴 Import & Reference Issues Report — AURA Frontend

All files in `myapp/src/` have been reviewed. Below are the issues found.

---

## 🚨 Critical (will crash the app)

### 1. `App.jsx` — Uses `useTheme` and `cls` but never imports them
- **Line 73**: `useTheme()` is called inside `ModeBadge`, `RiskCard`, `HandshakeIndicator`, `EnvironmentMetricRow`, and other inline components
- **Line 83**: `cls()` used everywhere
- **Fix**: Add `import { useTheme } from "./context/ThemeContext"` and `import { cls } from "./utils/cls"`
- These functions are defined **locally inside `MyComponent.jsx`** but NOT in `App.jsx`, so inline components in App.jsx that reference them will crash

### 2. `WalletPage.jsx` — `wallets` state never declared
- **Line 28**: `wallets.reduce(...)` is called but `wallets` is never declared via `useState`
- **Line 95**: `wallets.map(...)` used in JSX
- **Fix**: Add `const [wallets, setWallets] = useState([]);` before line 28

### 3. `TokensPage.jsx` — Calls `getUserWallets` and `setWallets` which are not imported/defined
- **Line 22**: `getUserWallets(userId)` is called, but only `getWalletTokens` is imported from `api.js`
- **Line 24**: `setWallets(data)` is called, but `wallets`/`setWallets` state is never declared
- **Fix**: Either import `getUserWallets` from `../api/api`, or replace the logic with `getWalletTokens`; declare `const [wallets, setWallets] = useState([])`

### 4. `TokensPage.jsx` — Undefined variable `w` in JSX
- **Line 78**: `{w.wallet_type}` — `w` is not defined in this scope (it's the loop variable from `tokens.map((tk, i) => ...)`, not `w`)
- **Fix**: Replace `w.wallet_type` with appropriate token property like `tk.amount`

---

## ⚠️ Moderate (unused imports / redundant code)

### 5. `App.jsx` — Unused import `Outlet`
- **Line 19**: `import { Outlet, useLocation, useNavigate } from "react-router-dom"`
- `Outlet` is never used in `App.jsx` (it's used in `AppLayout.jsx` instead)
- `useLocation` and `useNavigate` are also unused in `App.jsx`
- **Fix**: Remove `Outlet, useLocation, useNavigate` from the import

### 6. `App.jsx` — Unused Lucide icon imports
- **Line 23–29**: Many icons imported (`Send`, `Inbox`, `Radio`, `Bluetooth`, `Volume2`, `Sun`, `QrCode`, `Wifi`, `Zap`, `Activity`, `Battery`, `Mic`, `Eye`, `Gauge`, `Fingerprint`, `Clock`, `ShieldAlert`, `CheckCircle2`, `Loader2`, `ScanLine`, `Cpu`, `Signal`) are used in inline component definitions, BUT those same components also exist as separate files in `components/ui/`. This creates **duplicate definitions**.

### 7. `App.jsx` — Inline component definitions duplicate extracted components
- `ModeBadge`, `RiskCard`, `HandshakeIndicator`, `EnvironmentMetricRow` are all defined inline in `App.jsx` (lines 72–187) **AND** exist as separate component files in `components/ui/`
- The inline versions reference `useTheme` and `cls` which aren't imported in `App.jsx`
- **Fix**: Remove the inline component definitions from `App.jsx` since they are unused (routes use the page files which import from `components/ui/`)

### 8. `Badge.jsx` — Unused imports
- **Line 3–4**: `useTheme` and `T` are imported but never used in the component
- **Fix**: Remove those imports

### 9. `Button.jsx` — Unused imports
- **Line 3–4**: `useTheme` and `T` are imported but never used in the component
- **Fix**: Remove those imports

### 10. `MiniLineChart.jsx` — Unused imports
- **Line 1**: `React` is imported but never used (not needed with modern JSX transform)
- **Line 2–3**: `useTheme` and `T` are imported but never used
- **Fix**: Remove all three

### 11. `MyComponent.jsx` — Entire file appears to be legacy/dead code
- This 1400+ line file is a monolithic version of the entire app that was later refactored into separate page/component files
- It imports `usePageLoad` from `./hooks/usePageLoad` but also **redefines** `usePageLoad` locally (line 494)
- It defines its own `ThemeCtx`, `useTheme`, `cls`, `normalizeVariant` locally, duplicating the extracted utilities
- **Fix**: If this file is not imported anywhere (it's not referenced in routes), consider **deleting it entirely**

### 12. `TransactionsPage.jsx` — Duplicate React imports
- **Line 10**: `import { useState } from "react"`
- **Line 15**: `import { useEffect } from "react"`
- **Fix**: Combine into `import { useState, useEffect } from "react"`

### 13. `TransactionsPage.jsx` — Duplicate Lucide imports
- **Line 9**: `import { ArrowRightLeft, Search } from "lucide-react"`
- **Line 13**: `import { ArrowDown } from "lucide-react"`
- **Fix**: Combine into one import statement

### 14. `WalletPage.jsx` — Duplicate Lucide imports
- **Line 12**: `import { Wallet, ArrowUp, ArrowDown } from "lucide-react"` (ArrowUp and ArrowDown unused)
- **Line 16**: `import { AlertTriangle } from "lucide-react"`
- **Line 17**: `import { PlusCircle } from "lucide-react"`
- **Fix**: Combine into a single import + remove unused (`ArrowUp`, `ArrowDown`)

---

## 📋 Summary

| Severity | Count | Files Affected |
|----------|-------|----------------|
| 🚨 Critical | 4 | `App.jsx`, `WalletPage.jsx`, `TokensPage.jsx` |
| ⚠️ Moderate | 10 | `App.jsx`, `Badge.jsx`, `Button.jsx`, `MiniLineChart.jsx`, `MyComponent.jsx`, `TransactionsPage.jsx`, `WalletPage.jsx` |

> **Recommendation**: Fix the 4 critical issues first — they will cause runtime crashes. Then clean up unused imports and remove `MyComponent.jsx` if it's truly dead code.
